Sermon of St. John. In Ghirlandajo's (S. Maria Novella) & in Andrea del Sarto's (Scalzo) frescoes ([Heinrich] Wölfflin, Classic Art, [London: Phaidon Press, 1953], p. 162) Christ is present in the background on the left as he also is in the Baptistery mosaics. Look up Künstler in Jameson, History of Our Lord [= Anna Jameson, The history of Our Lord as exemplified in works of art: With that of his types; St. John the Baptist; and other persons of the Old and New Testament, London: Longman, Green, 1890] I, p. 305f. Quercia: Font in Siena Baptistery, Andrea Pisano: Florence, Baptistery door.
